# Vercel honors .gitignore by default. .gitignore lists src/data/snapshot/ as
# build-time material to keep the working tree clean. But on Vercel we cannot
# regenerate the snapshot (the monorepo's docs/, outputs/ are not uploaded),
# so we whitelist the pre-built snapshot here so it ships with the bundle.
#
# Workflow:
#   1. local: `npm run snapshot` materializes src/data/snapshot/
#   2. local: `vercel --prod` uploads apps/research/ (snapshot included via this whitelist)
#   3. remote: `prebuild` script no-ops because VERCEL=1 and manifest exists
#   4. remote: `next build` traces snapshot into lambda via outputFileTracingIncludes

!src/data/snapshot
!src/data/snapshot/**

# Standard ignores Vercel should respect regardless of .gitignore quirks.
.next/
node_modules/
.synapse/
**/.synapse/
*.tsbuildinfo
